==English==
{{webster}}
===Etymology===
From [[w:Latin|Latin]][[Category:Latin derivations]] [[bitumen]]: compare with [[w:French language|French]][[category:French derivations]] [[bitume]]. Compare with [[Béton]].

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''bitumen'''
#Mineral [[pitch]]; a black, [[tarry]] substance, burning with a bright flame; [[Jew's pitch]]. It occurs as an abundant natural product in many places, as on the shores of the Dead and Caspian Seas. It is used in [[cement]]s, in the construction of [[pavement]]s, etc. See [[asphalt]].
#By extension, any one of the natural [[hydrocarbon]]s, including the hard, solid, [[brittle]] varieties called asphalt, the semisolid [[maltha]] and mineral [[tar]]s, the oily [[petroleum]]s, and even the light, volatile [[naphtha]]s. 

[[Category: English nouns]]

